This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) tasks, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on using a variant of recurrent neural networks (LSTM) for NLP tasks, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves using contextual features (e.g., topics) to improve performance, which is a common theme in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language understanding (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on large-scale datasets, which is a relevant topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL).
